If $j$ and $k$ are inversely proportional and $j = 42$ when $k = 56$, what is the value of $j$ when $k = 32$? Express your answer as a decimal rounded to the nearest tenth.
Here we have inverse proportionality, so $j(k) = c$ for some constant $c$. Plugging in the values $j = 42$ when $k = 56$, we have $c = 42 \cdot 56 = 2352$. So we have $j(k) = 2352/k$. We then set $k = 32$ and evaluate:
\begin{align*}
j(32) &= \frac{2352}{32} \\
&\approx \boxed{73.5}.
\end{align*}
And that’s our answer, which is approximately 73.5.
